DPES2_2: I develop strong feelings of closeness to people easily.

IRI2_1: I daydream and fantasize, with some regularity, about things that might happen to me.
IRI2_2: I often have tender, concerned feelings for people less fortunate than me.
IRI2_3: I sometimes find it difficult to see things from the "other guy's" point of view.
IRI2_4: Sometimes I don't feel very sorry for other people when they are having problems.
IRI2_5: I really get involved with the feelings of the characters in a novel.
IRI2_6: In emergency situations, I feel apprehensive and ill-at-ease.
IRI2_7: I am usually objective when I watch a movie or play, and I don't often get completely caught up in it.
IRI2_8: I try to look at everybody's side of a disagreement before I make a decision.
IRI2_9: When I see someone being taken advantage of, I feel kind of protective towards them.
IRI2_10: I sometimes feel helpless when I am in the middle of a very emotional situation.
IRI2_11: I sometimes try to understand my friends better by imagining how things look from their perspective.
IRI2_12: Becoming extremely involved in a good book or movie is somewhat rare for me.
IRI2_13: When I see someone get hurt, I tend to remain calm.
IRI2_14: Other people's misfortunes do not usually disturb me a great deal.
ATTN2_2: It is important that you pay attention. Please select "A - Does Not Describe Me Well".
IRI2_15: If I'm sure I'm right about something, I don't waste much time listening to other people's arguments.
IRI2_16: After seeing a play or movie, I have felt as though I were one of the characters.
IRI2_17: Being in a tense emotional situation scares me.
IRI2_18: When I see someone being treated unfairly, I sometimes don't feel very much pity for them.
IRI2_19: I am usually pretty effective in dealing with emergencies.
IRI2_20: I am often quite touched by things that I see happen.
IRI2_21: I believe that there are two sides to every question and I try to look at them both.
IRI2_22: I would describe myself as a pretty soft-hearted person.
IRI2_23: When I watch a good movie, I can very easily put myself in the place of a leading character.
IRI2_24: I tend to lose control during emergencies.
IRI2_25: When I'm upset at someone, I usually try to "put myself in their shoes" for a while.
IRI2_26: When I am reading an interesting story or novel, I imagine how I would feel if the events in the story were happening to me.
IRI2_27: When I see someone who badly needs help in an emergency, I go to pieces.
IRI2_28: Before criticizing somebody, I try to imagine how I would feel if I were in their place.
